'''Level 315''' is the 316<sup>th</sup> level of [[Backrooms Wiki|The Backrooms]].
==Description==
{{Blurimage|file=Level305-1.webp|caption=An image of '''Level 315'''.}}
{{Blurimage|file=Level315-4.jpg|caption=Another image of the level.}}
{{Blurimage|file=Level315-2.jpg|caption=A photograph of one of the lower floors.}}
'''Level 315''' is a huge restaurant with tables and chairs in various colors, but mostly red. The walls of the building are made of concrete covered with red wallpaper. The floor is covered with a carpet and lit by ceiling lighting. There may be porcelain plates and cutlery on the tables in the restaurant, and sometimes there is food on these plates. These foods should not be consumed. As a result of an experiment by [[M.E.G.]], all 3 subjects who ate these dishes, more specifically steak and mashed potatoes, became ill after about half an hour. And although necessary medical interventions were applied, they could not be saved and died. There may also be wooden shelves full of food, which should not be consumed in the same way. These shelves may contain salt, pepper, and sugar, as well as complete meals such as chops, steaks, fish, and salads. In addition, the building may have decorations such as paintings and plants.

The level's size is immeasurably large, with an estimated infinite number of floors. Some floors might consist of a single enormous hall, while others might be made up of several smaller rooms. Unintelligible Chinese text covers a large portion of the level's walls. Additionally, there may be television displays mounted on the walls in certain parts of the level. These televisions broadcast streams at random times, but all that is visible are blank screens of various colors and odd ringing noises. The restaurant's speakers play soothing, quiet music throughout the level. Along with that, the majority of the level is filled with the loud noises of air conditioning.

It has been noted that the atmosphere is generally brighter and the floors tend to be wider as one goes up the level, whereas the level becomes darker and the floors tend to be narrower as one goes down. In addition, the lower floors generally seem to have more resources than the floors above, such as food and drink or flashlights. However, the lower floors are much more likely to have hazardous substances such as [[Object 33|Memory Flame]] than the floors above. Wanderers have reported that they found themselves on one of the lower floors when they first entered the level, but it is also possible to start on the upper floors.

Random doors mounted on walls may be found within the level. Some of these doors are unlocked while others are locked, and the locked ones cannot be opened by muscle power or tools of any kind. Unlocked doors will usually open to another random part of the level, but some may open directly to [[The Void]] or another level. It is not recommended to no-clip at this level, as the chance of falling into [[The Void]] is extremely high. According to a [[B.W.O.]] researcher, three of his friends were suddenly lost at the level, and it is likely that they no-clipped and fell into [[The Void]]. Additionally, hazardous substances such as broken glass and [[Object 33|Memory Flame]] drops may be found on the floor. There also may be boxes scattered on the ground around the level. These boxes are mostly empty; however, the ones that aren't empty are often filled with harmful substances such as [[Object 33|Memory Flame]], [[Object 44|Cashew Water]] or [[Object 12|Liquid Pain]].

Some parts of the level may have windows showing the outside. It is not possible to damage these windows in any way and climb out. As visible through the windows, the outside of the level consists of empty asphalt roads in empty plains. Although these roads are mostly empty, occasionally, empty cars with no driver can be seen passing quite fast on these roads. Observations of the sky have shown that time is at least several times slower in the level than in [[The Frontrooms]]. Furthermore, the night is much longer in the level than the day, and it is quite rare to experience the level during the daytime. 

The wanderers at the level have reported hearing strange whispers or footsteps as time progressed, and these sounds increased as time went on. This is thought to be a psychological effect of the level on the wanderers. Experts recommend drinking [[Object 1|Almond Water]] once these noises start to appear. If the noises do not decrease, it is advisable just to ignore them completely and focus on the objective. 

{{Blurimage|file=Level315-3.jpg|caption=An image of the kitchen.}}
In the back of the level, there is an area known as '''the kitchen'''. The kitchen is the room where every meal is made. It is highly discouraged to eat the food that "The Cook" prepares here since it is unknown what is in it. The oven is large enough for an adult to fit comfortably within, supporting the hypothesis that humans were inside the food. However, this hypothesis has yet to be proved. Nonetheless, what happened to the wanderers captured by "The Cook" is unknown, and no trace of them remains.

[[B.W.O.]] has recently found a notebook resembling a diary lying on the ground, with a single page of notes written inside.
<br style="clear:both" />
<div class="notething">
<br><div style="text-align: center; font-family:Nunito; font-size: 25px">Recovered Note</div><br><center><div style="font-family:Nunito">
<div class="image">[[File:Level305-23323.jpg|link=|center|300x300px]]</div><br><br>
<div style="text-align: justify">
Oh, man, I think it's been a day or two since I've arrived here. It is a bit hard to tell the time of day. So the plan now is to write here about my experiences with this place and then... I guess I'll try to find a way out of here. Well, first of all, let me tell you what's going on around. Everywhere, and I mean EVERYWHERE, there are tables and chairs. Some of these tables have food on them, and some have leftovers. The food doesn't look safe to me, so I didn't taste any of it, even though I'm hungry. In fact, at one point I could have sworn I saw a dead body sitting on one of the chairs, looking like it had been poisoned. So yes, there is a very high chance that the food is poisoned.

I found doors in certain parts of the level, doors that seemed out of place. These doors were like portals, leading to unrelated parts of the level. However, a door I opened led directly to [[The Void]]. I'm lucky I have good reflexes, otherwise I would be writing this while floating in there. A few doors seemed to lead to different levels. Honestly, I could have entered them to leave this place, but those seemed even worse than here, so I stayed here.

To be honest, sometimes I feel like I'm losing my mind. I hear whispers and other sounds coming from nearby, but when I look there, I see nothing. What's worse is that I have no idea if this is just me or if this is just how this place is in general. I'm trying to drink as much [[Object 1|Almond Water]] as I can, but the voices aren't going away, in fact, they've started to get louder lately.

Also, this place is quite empty. I don't think I've seen any entities around. Well, except when the lights went out, that is.
</div></div></center><br>
</div>

==Entities==
===The Cook===
The Cook is the entity responsible for running the level, the restaurant. The cook prepares every dish at the level and captures any wanderer he finds. The cook's appearance is identical to that of a standard cook, but without a face, he seems to be an exceptionally powerful [[Entity 9|faceling]] as he is faster and stronger in terms of muscle strength than the other [[Entity 9|Facelings]]. "The Kitchen" is The Cook's primary workspace, and he may visit the main restaurant during his free time. The wanderers must hide to survive while he chases them. Under tables and chairs is the most ideal hiding spot; there are no other suitable hiding spots.
