<div style="background-position-x: 50%; background-size: 100% 200%; background-repeat: no-repeat; position: fixed; width: 100vw; height: 100vh; z-index: 2; opacity: 0.8; left: 50%; transform: translateX(-50%); animation: sillyanim2 3s infinite alternate;"></div>

<div style="position: relative; display: flex; justify-content: center; width: 100%; margin-top: 100px; overflow: hidden; z-index: 3;">
<div style="width: 80%; text-align: center; color: #f1f3fc; font-family: VT323; font-size: 20px; letter-spacing: 2px; text-shadow: 1px 1px 5px #670000; font-weight: bold;">

<div style="font-size: 35px; opacity: 1; letter-spacing: 5px"><span style="font-family: Nunito">File #1</span><div style="display: inline-block; animation: sillyanim 0.75s infinite alternate">:</div> <span style="font-family: Nunito">Dinner-Time Event</span></div>
<br><br>
<div class="text">
"Every once in a while, The Cook will come out of his kitchen, all the lights will be turned off, and the building will be plunged into darkness. A fog will fill the air, and the wanderer will soon realize that it is the smoke from the incredibly hot soup that The Cook has brought. The Cook will move towards the wanderer he sees, and approach them in a friendly manner, offering them some of the food he has brought. Eating this food will result in death because it is either poisonous or extremely hot. The way to avoid this is to hide from The Cook or run away."
</div>
<div class="text" style="animation-delay: 0.25s;">
I was warned before entering the level about the chances of something like this happening. Even though I knew it was going to happen to me, I kept going, I kept moving forward. I remember the first moment my friend and I entered the level, the calm music playing from the speakers sending shivers down my spine, and I was bracing myself for anything that might happen, stepping carefully to avoid the harmful substances on the carpet, praying that the lights wouldn't go out... But it did.
</div>
<div class="text" style="animation-delay: 0.50s;">
Around the third hour of walking around the level, the music playing through the speakers suddenly stopped. It was as if I knew what we were dealing with. Right after the music stopped, the lights suddenly turned off. I grabbed my friend who thought the power had gone out and started running, looking for a place to hide. The words “Dinner Time” written on the screens on the walls gave me the creeps. My friend and I kept running until we saw the figure a little ahead of us. The figure was in darkness, faceless and wearing a chef's hat. I knew who he was the moment I saw him. My friend, unaware of what was happening, was right behind me and we started running in the opposite direction. Having carefully read from the files what to do and what not to do during the Dinner-Time Event, I quickly hid under a dining table. I wanted to call out to my friend, but something stopped me.
</div>
<div class="text" style="animation-delay: 0.75s;">
I didn't want to die.
</div>
<div class="text" style="animation-delay: 1s;">
My friend kept running and after a while, both The Cook and my friend disappeared. I could guess what had happened to him, but I didn't want to think about it. I closed my eyes tightly. After a while the lights came back on and I was safe. I searched desperately for my friend for a while, but I was aware that I wouldn't find him. After wandering around for a while, my mission was over, I had gathered all the information I needed to collect on the level. I started looking for an exit. Soon I passed through a purple door and reached [[Level 246|the shores where the moonlight shone]]. I contacted the team, I told them everything. Now I'm resting, I'm scared.
</div>
<div class="text" style="animation-delay: 1.25s;">
And now here I am, sitting here looking at the only photograph we have of the event.
</div>
