==Settlements==
Level 315 has a few known bases.
{{Blurimage|file=Level315Wanderersplace.png|caption=An abandoned base belonging to one of the old groups. Once thought to have been home to many wanderers, the location now stands empty.}}
===Wanderer's Place===
Defining themselves as wanderer-friendly, Wanderer's Place is a group within Level 315 that aims to befriend and trade with any lost wanderers. They have managed to purify the poisonous food found within the level somehow and use it as their main source of nutrition, while also feeding it to the wanderers they encounter. Since there are no recorded instances of anyone having died from eating these dishes, Wanderer's Place's filtering techniques appear to be safe. As the group has adopted a policy of complete peace, it has no enemies.

===Anti-Cooks===
Known as Anti-Cooks, the group aims to kill the only entity at that level, "The Cook." They are mostly friendly toward other wanderers and have collaborated with some small groups, including Wanderer’s Place, in the past. It is estimated that the Anti-Cooks have been active for approximately 40 years. Over the past 40 years, the group has engaged in numerous battles with the Cook but has not yet managed to inflict significant damage on it.

===L.E.C. Outpost D===
Outpost D, a minor research base belonging to the Liminality Experiment Colonies group, is a rarely used outpost. The number of research projects conducted at this outpost peaked in the early 2010's but gradually declined due to the dangers of the level, reaching rock bottom after a massacre involving the Cook. Although it is still occasionally used today, no active members are working there currently.

Besides the ones mentioned above, there are many other small groups at this level, but none of them have shown any success worth mentioning. In addition to these, there are other groups that used to be among the major groups at the level but have since shrunk, or that used to exist but no longer exist today.

==Entrances and Exits==
===Entrances===
There are currently four known entrances to '''Level 315'''.
*Kitchens in [[Level 5]] have a chance of leading here.
*Entering a building labeled "Cook's Place" in any level.
*[[Level 98]] may suddenly transfer into this level without warning.
===Exits===
*If one entered the building labeled "Cook's Place", exiting back using the entrance door will take one back to the level they were before '''Level 315'''.
*Finding and entering a door hanging from the ceiling might take one to [[Level 28]].
*Finding a neon door and entering it will take one to [[Level 154]].
*Entering a purple door will take one to [[Level 246]].
*Although inconsistent, noclipping anywhere occasionally sends one here to [[Level 960]].

